{"word":"David","slug":"david","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>David</b> <a href=\"#/H1732\">H1732</a> <br/> 1. King of Israel<br/> - Genealogy of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=8&chapter=4&verse=22'>Rth 4:22</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=16&verse=11'>1Sa 16:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=17&verse=12'>1Sa 17:12</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=2&verse=15'>1Ch 2:15</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=1&verse=6'>Mat 1:6</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=42&chapter=3&verse=38'>Luk 3:38</a> <br/> - A shepherd<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=16&verse=11'>1Sa 16:11</a> <br/> - Kills a lion and a bear<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=17&verse=36'>1Sa 17:36</a> <br/> - Anointed king, while a youth, by the prophet Samuel, and inspired<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=16&verse=1'>1Sa 16:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=16&verse=13'>1Sa 16:13</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=89&verse=37'>Psa 89:37</a> <br/> - Chosen of God<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=78&verse=70'>Psa 78:70</a> <br/> - Described to Saul<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=16&verse=18'>1Sa 16:18</a> <br/> - Detailed as armorbearer and musician at Saul's court<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=16&verse=23'>1Sa 16:23</a> <br/> - Slays Goliath<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=17'>1Sa 17</a> <br/> - Love of Jonathan for<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=18&verse=4'>1Sa 18:4</a> <br/> - Popularity and discreetness of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=18'>1Sa 18</a> <br/> - Saul's jealousy of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=18&verse=30'>1Sa 18:30</a> <br/> - Is defrauded of Merab, and given Michal to wife<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=18&verse=27'>1Sa 18:27</a> <br/> - Jonathan intercedes for<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=19&verse=7'>1Sa 19:7</a> <br/> - Probably writes Psalm 11:1-7 at this period of his life<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=11&verse=7'>Psa 11:7</a> <br/> - Conducts a campaign against, and defeats, the Philistines<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=19&verse=8'>1Sa 19:8</a> <br/> - Saul attempts to slay him; he escapes to Ramah, and dwells at Naioth, whither Saul pursues him<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=19&verse=24'>1Sa 19:24</a> <br/> - About this time writes Psalm 59<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=59'>Psa 59</a> <br/> - Returns, and Jonathan makes covenant with him<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=20'>1Sa 20</a> <br/> - Escapes by way of Nob, where he obtains shewbread and Goliath's sword from Abimelech<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=21&verse=6'>1Sa 21:6</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=12&verse=4'>Mat 12:4</a> <br/> - Escapes to Gath<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=21&verse=15'>1Sa 21:15</a> <br/> - At this time probably writes Psalms 34, 35, Psalm 52:1-9, Psalm 56:1-13, Psalm 120:1-7<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=34'>Psa 34</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=52&verse=9'>Psa 52:9</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=56&verse=13'>Psa 56:13</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=120&verse=7'>Psa 120:7</a> <br/> - Recruits an army of insurgents, goes to Moab, returns to Hareth<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=22'>1Sa 22</a> <br/> - Probably writes Psalm 17:1-15, Psalm 35, Psalm 52:1-9, Psalm 58:1-11, Psalm 64:1-10, Psalm 109, Psalm 142:1-7<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=17&verse=15'>Psa 17:15</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=35'>Psa 35</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=52&verse=9'>Psa 52:9</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=58&verse=11'>Psa 58:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=64&verse=10'>Psa 64:10</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=109'>Psa 109</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=142&verse=7'>Psa 142:7</a> <br/> - Saves Keilah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=23&verse=13'>1Sa 23:13</a> <br/> - Makes second covenant with Jonathan<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=23&verse=18'>1Sa 23:18</a> <br/> - Goes to the wilderness of Ziph, is betrayed to Saul<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=23&verse=26'>1Sa 23:26</a> <br/> - Writes a psalm on the betrayal, Psalm 54:1-7, and probably Psalms 22, 31, 34, Psalm 140:1-13<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=54&verse=7'>Psa 54:7</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=22'>Psa 22</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=31'>Psa 31</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=34'>Psa 34</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=140&verse=13'>Psa 140:13</a> <br/> - Saul is diverted from pursuit of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=23&verse=28'>1Sa 23:28</a> <br/> - At this time probably writes Psalm 12:1-8, 22<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=12&verse=8'>Psa 12:8</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=22'>Psa 22</a> <br/> - Goes to En-Gedi<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=23&verse=29'>1Sa 23:29</a><br/> b Refrains from slaying Saul<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=24'>1Sa 24</a><br/> - Writes Psalm 57:1-11<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=57&verse=11'>Psa 57:11</a> <br/> - Covenants with Saul<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=26'>1Sa 26</a> <br/> - Marries Nabal's widow, Abigail, and Ahinoam<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=25'>1Sa 25</a> <br/> - Dwells in the wilderness of Ziph, has opportunity to slay Saul, but takes his spear only, Saul is contrite<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=26'>1Sa 26</a> <br/> - Flees to Achish and dwells in Ziklag<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=27&verse=12'>1Sa 27:12</a> <br/> - List of men who join him<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=12&verse=22'>1Ch 12:22</a> <br/> - Conducts an expedition against Amalekites, misstates the facts to Achish<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=27&verse=12'>1Sa 27:12</a> <br/> - At this time probably writes Psalm 141:1-10<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=141&verse=10'>Psa 141:10</a> <br/> - Is refused permission to accompany the Philistines to battle against the Israelitesh<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=28&verse=2'>1Sa 28:2</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=29&verse=11'>1Sa 29:11</a> <br/> - Rescues the people of Ziklag, who had been captured by the Amalekites<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=30'>1Sa 30</a> <br/> - Probably writes Psalm 13:1-6<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=13&verse=6'>Psa 13:6</a> <br/> - Death and burial of Saul and his sons<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=31&verse=13'>1Sa 31:13</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=21&verse=1'>2Sa 21:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=21&verse=14'>2Sa 21:14</a> <br/> - Slays the murderer of Saul<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=1&verse=16'>2Sa 1:16</a> <br/> - Lamentation over Saul<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=1&verse=27'>2Sa 1:27</a> <br/> - Dwells one year and four months at Ziklag<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=27&verse=7'>1Sa 27:7</a> <br/> - Goes to Hebron, and is anointed king by Judah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=2&verse=4'>2Sa 2:4</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=2&verse=11'>2Sa 2:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=5&verse=5'>2Sa 5:5</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=2&verse=11'>1Ki 2:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=3&verse=4'>1Ch 3:4</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=11&verse=3'>1Ch 11:3</a> <br/> - List of those who join him at Hebron<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=12&verse=40'>1Ch 12:40</a> <br/> - Ish-Bosheth, son of Saul, crowned<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=2'>2Sa 2</a> <br/> - David wages war against, and defeats, Ish-Bosheth<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=2&verse=32'>2Sa 2:32</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=3&verse=4'>2Sa 3:4</a> <br/> - Demands the restoration of Michal, his wife<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=3&verse=16'>2Sa 3:16</a> <br/> - Abner revolts from Ish-Bosheth, and joins David, but is slain by Joab<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=3'>2Sa 3</a> <br/> - Punishes Ish-Bosheth's murderers<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=4&verse=12'>2Sa 4:12</a> <br/> - Anointed king over all Israel, after reigning over Judah at Hebron seven years and six months, and reigns thirty-three years<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=2&verse=11'>2Sa 2:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=5&verse=5'>2Sa 5:5</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=3&verse=4'>1Ch 3:4</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=11&verse=3'>1Ch 11:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=12&verse=40'>1Ch 12:40</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=29&verse=27'>1Ch 29:27</a> <br/> - Makes conquest of Jerusalem<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=5&verse=6'>2Sa 5:6</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=11&verse=8'>1Ch 11:8</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=23&chapter=29&verse=1'>Isa 29:1</a> <br/> - Builds a palace<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=5&verse=11'>2Sa 5:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=2&verse=3'>2Ch 2:3</a> <br/> - Friendship of, with Hiram, king of Tyre<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=5&verse=11'>2Sa 5:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=5&verse=1'>1Ki 5:1</a> <br/> - Prospered of God<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=5&verse=10'>2Sa 5:10</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=11&verse=9'>1Ch 11:9</a> <br/> - Fame of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=14&verse=17'>1Ch 14:17</a> <br/> - Philistines make war against, and are defeated by him<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=5&verse=25'>2Sa 5:25</a> <br/> - Assembles thirty thousand men to escort the ark to Jerusalem with music and thanksgiving<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=6&verse=5'>2Sa 6:5</a> <br/> - Uzzah is stricken when he attempts to steady the ark<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=6&verse=11'>2Sa 6:11</a> <br/> - David is terrified, and leaves the ark at the house of Obed-Edom<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=6&verse=11'>2Sa 6:11</a> <br/> - After three months brings the ark to Jerusalem with dancing and great joy<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=6&verse=16'>2Sa 6:16</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=13&verse=14'>1Ch 13:14</a> <br/> - Organized the tabernacle service<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=9&verse=22'>1Ch 9:22</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=15&verse=24'>1Ch 15:24</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=16&verse=6'>1Ch 16:6</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=16&verse=43'>1Ch 16:43</a> <br/> - Offers sacrifice, distributes gifts, and blesses the people<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=6&verse=19'>2Sa 6:19</a> <br/> - Michal upbraids him for his religious enthusiasm<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=6&verse=23'>2Sa 6:23</a> <br/> - Desires to build a temple, is forbidden, but receives promise that his seed should reign forever<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=7&verse=16'>2Sa 7:16</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=23&verse=5'>2Sa 23:5</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=17&verse=14'>1Ch 17:14</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=6&verse=16'>2Ch 6:16</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=89&verse=4'>Psa 89:4</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=132&verse=12'>Psa 132:12</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=15&verse=16'>Act 15:16</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=45&chapter=15&verse=12'>Rom 15:12</a> <br/> - Interpretation and fulfillment of this prophecy<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=13&verse=23'>Act 13:23</a> <br/> - At this time, probably, writes Psalm 15:1-5, Psalm 16:1-11, Psalm 24:1-10, Psalm 101:1-8, Psalm 138:1-8<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=15'>Psa 15</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=24&verse=10'>Psa 24:10</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=101&verse=8'>Psa 101:8</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=138&verse=8'>Psa 138:8</a> <br/> - Conquers the Philistines, Moabites, and Syria<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=8'>2Sa 8</a> <br/> - Treats Mephibosheth, the lame son of Saul, with great kindness<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=9&verse=6'>2Sa 9:6</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=19&verse=30'>2Sa 19:30</a> <br/> - Sends commissioners with a message of sympathy to Hanun, son of the king of Ammon; the message misinterpreted, and commissioners treated with indignity; David retaliates by invading his kingdom, and defeating the combined armies of the Ammonites and Syrians<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=10'>2Sa 10</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=19'>1Ch 19</a> <br/> - Probably writes Psalm 18, Psalm 20:1-9, Psalm 21:1-13<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=18'>Psa 18</a> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=20'>Psa 20</a> <br/> - Commits adultery with Bath-Sheba<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=11&verse=5'>2Sa 11:5</a> <br/> - Wickedly causes the death of Uriah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=11&verse=25'>2Sa 11:25</a> <br/> - Takes Bath-Sheba to be his wife<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=11&verse=27'>2Sa 11:27</a> <br/> - Is rebuked by the prophet Nathan<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=12&verse=14'>2Sa 12:14</a> <br/> - Repents of his crime and confesses his guilt<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=6&verse=10'>Psa 6:10</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=32&verse=11'>Psa 32:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=38'>Psa 38</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=51'>Psa 51</a> <br/> - Is chastised with grievous affliction on account of his crime<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=38'>Psa 38</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=41&verse=13'>Psa 41:13</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=69'>Psa 69</a> <br/> - Death of his infant son by Bath-Sheba<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=12&verse=23'>2Sa 12:23</a> <br/> - Solomon is born to<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=12&verse=25'>2Sa 12:25</a> <br/> - Ammonites defeated and tortured<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=12&verse=31'>2Sa 12:31</a> <br/> - Amnon's crime, his murder by Absalom, and Absalom's flight<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=13'>2Sa 13</a> <br/> - Absalom's return<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=14&verse=24'>2Sa 14:24</a> <br/> - Absalom's usurpation<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=14'>2Sa 14</a> <br/> - David's flight from Jerusalem<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=15&verse=37'>2Sa 15:37</a> <br/> - He probably writes, at this time, Psalm 5:1-12, Psalm 7, Psalm 26:1-12, Psalm 61:1-8, Psalm 63:1-11, Psalm 69, Psalm 70:1-5, 86, Psalm 143:1-12<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=5&verse=12'>Psa 5:12</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=7'>Psa 7</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=26&verse=12'>Psa 26:12</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=61&verse=8'>Psa 61:8</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=63&verse=11'>Psa 63:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=69'>Psa 69</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=86'>Psa 86</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=143&verse=12'>Psa 143:12</a> <br/> - Shimei curses him<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=16'>2Sa 16</a> <br/> - Crosses the Jordan<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=17&verse=29'>2Sa 17:29</a> <br/> - Absalom's defeat and death<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=18'>2Sa 18</a> <br/> - Laments the death of Absalom<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=18&verse=33'>2Sa 18:33</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=19&verse=4'>2Sa 19:4</a> <br/> - Upbraided by Joab<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=19&verse=7'>2Sa 19:7</a> <br/> - David upbraids the priests for not showing loyalty amid the murmurings of the people against him<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=19&verse=15'>2Sa 19:15</a> <br/> - Shimei sues for clemency<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=19&verse=23'>2Sa 19:23</a> <br/> - Mephibosheth sues for the king's favor<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=19&verse=30'>2Sa 19:30</a> <br/> - Barzillai rewarded<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=19&verse=40'>2Sa 19:40</a> <br/> - Judah accused by the ten tribes of stealing him away<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=19&verse=43'>2Sa 19:43</a> <br/> - Returns to Jerusalem<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=20&verse=3'>2Sa 20:3</a> <br/> - At this time, probably composes Psalm 27:1-14, Psalm 66, Psalm 122:1-9, Psalm 144:1-15<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=27&verse=14'>Psa 27:14</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=66'>Psa 66</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=122&verse=9'>Psa 122:9</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=144&verse=15'>Psa 144:15</a> <br/> - Sheba's conspiracy against David, and his death<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=20'>2Sa 20</a> <br/> - Makes Amasa general<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=19&verse=13'>2Sa 19:13</a> <br/> - Amasa is slain<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=20&verse=10'>2Sa 20:10</a> <br/> - Consigns seven sons of Saul to the Gibeonites to be slain to atone for Saul's persecution of the Gibeonites<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=21&verse=14'>2Sa 21:14</a> <br/> - Buries Saul's bones, and his sons'<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=21&verse=14'>2Sa 21:14</a> <br/> - Defeats the Philistines<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=21&verse=22'>2Sa 21:22</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=20&verse=8'>1Ch 20:8</a> <br/> - Takes the military strength of Israel without divine authority, and is reproved<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=24'>2Sa 24</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=21'>1Ch 21</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=27&verse=24'>1Ch 27:24</a> <br/> - Probably composes Psalm 30:1-12, Psalm 131:1-3<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=30&verse=12'>Psa 30:12</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=131&verse=3'>Psa 131:3</a> <br/> - Marries Abishag<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=1&verse